    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Names or appellations used to reference people who have died. Prime examples are honorary names given to a person after death in East Asia, particularly as given to royalty, nobles, and some others, used rather than the original personal name after death.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
